body:
The following example uses the `queryString` operator to query for
movies with the title `Rocky` and either `IV`, `4`, or
`Four` at path `title` in the `movies` collection. In the
following query, a field is specified in the `defaultPath`,
but no fields are specified in the `query`. The query includes
a [$project](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/project) stage to exclude all fields except
`title`.

```javascript
db.movies.aggregate([
  {
    $search: {
      "queryString": {
        "defaultPath": "title",
        "query": "Rocky AND (IV OR 4 OR Four)"
      }
    }
  },
  {
    $project: {
      "_id": 0,
      "title": 1
    }
  }
])
```

For this query, MongoDB Search performs a search at `defaultPath`
because there are no fields in the `query`. It returns the
following results:

```json
{ "title" : "Rocky IV" }
```
